<div class="mv-create-jtr-wrapper"><a href="#mv-creation-35-jtr" class="mv-create-jtr mv-create-jtr-slot-v2 mv-create-jtr-button-hollow mv-create-jtr-button-uppercase"><svg class="mv-create-jtr-caret" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="1.1"  viewBox="0 0 444.819 444.819" width="16px" height="16px"><path d="M434.252,114.203l-21.409-21.416c-7.419-7.04-16.084-10.561-25.975-10.561c-10.095,0-18.657,3.521-25.7,10.561 L222.41,231.549L83.653,92.791c-7.042-7.04-15.606-10.561-25.697-10.561c-9.896,0-18.559,3.521-25.979,10.561l-21.128,21.416 C3.615,121.436,0,130.099,0,140.188c0,10.277,3.619,18.842,10.848,25.693l185.864,185.865c6.855,7.23,15.416,10.848,25.697,10.848 c10.088,0,18.75-3.617,25.977-10.848l185.865-185.865c7.043-7.044,10.567-15.608,10.567-25.693 C444.819,130.287,441.295,121.629,434.252,114.203z"/></svg> Jump to Recipe</a></div><style>.mv-create-jtr-wrapper{margin-bottom:20px}a.mv-create-jtr-link{display:inline-block;padding:10px 10px 10px 0;color:#333;font-size:16px;text-decoration:none!important;-webkit-transition:color .5s;transition:color .5s}a.mv-create-jtr-link:hover,a.mv-create-jtr-link:focus{color:#666}.mv-create-jtr-link .mv-create-jtr-caret{margin-right:5px;padding-top:6px;fill:#333}.mv-create-jtr-link:hover .mv-create-jtr-caret,.mv-create-jtr-link:focus .mv-create-jtr-caret{fill:#666}a.mv-create-jtr-button-hollow{display:inline-block;padding:.75em 1.5em;border:1px solid #333;color:#333;background:transparent;box-shadow:none;text-shadow:none;font-size:16px;text-align:center;text-decoration:none!important;cursor:pointer;-webkit-transition:background .5s;transition:background .5s}a.mv-create-jtr-button-hollow:hover,a.mv-create-jtr-button-hollow:focus{border:1px solid #666;color:#666;background:transparent;box-shadow:none}.mv-create-jtr-button-hollow .mv-create-jtr-caret{margin-right:5px;padding-top:6px;fill:#333}.mv-create-jtr-button-hollow:hover .mv-create-jtr-caret,.mv-create-jtr-button-hollow:focus .mv-create-jtr-caret{fill:#666}.mv-create-jtr-button-uppercase{text-transform:uppercase}</style><p class="p1"><span class="s1">Peparenjaci are something like a Croatian version of gingerbread cookies but with lots of black pepper as one of the main ingredients. </span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">The history of paprenjak dates back to the Renaissance, and was mentioned by August Šenoa, a famous Croatian author, in his &#8220;Zlatarevo zlato.&#8221; Nowadays they are becoming more and more valuable and a Croatian symbol and one of the <a href="https://www.chasingthedonkey.com/what-to-buy-in-croatia-souvenirs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">most popular souvenirs</a> you can take home with you.</span></p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-51374 aligncenter" src="https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Croatian-Cooking_Black-Pepper-Cookies-Recipe_PIN.png" alt="Croatian Cooking_Black Pepper Cookies Recipe" width="450" height="675" srcset="https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Croatian-Cooking_Black-Pepper-Cookies-Recipe_PIN.png 450w, https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/Croatian-Cooking_Black-Pepper-Cookies-Recipe_PIN-167x250.png 167w" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px"  loading="eager" fetchpriority="high"/></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">The <a href="https://www.chasingthedonkey.com/croatian-medenjaci-recipe/" target="_blank">recipe for these tasty cookies</a> is straightforward, but when you combine flour, walnuts, and honey with aromatic spices and pepper, you get something so unique and special that I think it&#8217;s really worth getting your kitchen messy for!</span></p>
<p class="p1">They are usually made at Christmas time, although<a href="https://www.chasingthedonkey.com/serbian-souvenirs-from-serbia-travel-blog/" target="_blank">&nbsp;you can buy</a> them in souvenir shops all year long as a souvenir. One of the main characteristics is that wooden mold is used for shaping and which you can also <a href="https://www.chasingthedonkey.com/albanian-souvenirs-what-to-buy-in-albania/" target="_blank">buy as a souvenir</a>.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-49929" src="https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-28.jpg" alt="How To Make Paprenjaci Recipe 28" width="900" height="884" srcset="https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-28.jpg 900w, https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-28-250x246.jpg 250w, https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-28-768x754.jpg 768w, https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-28-735x722.jpg 735w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px"  loading="lazy" fetchpriority="low"/></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">They are best if made at least 10-15 <a href="https://www.chasingthedonkey.com/one-day-in-mostar-bosnia-and-herzegovina-blog/" target="_blank">days before</a> eating as they get better and better while stored in an airtight container.</span></p>
<p class="p1"><span class="s1">It seems reasonable to mention that there are two different types of Paprenjak, one is from Hvar, and it doesn&#8217;t contain black pepper, and the other is from <a href="https://www.chasingthedonkey.com/travel-croatia-things-to-do-in-zagreb/" target="_blank">Zagreb</a>, where pepper is what makes them so unique.</span></p>
<div id='gallery-1' class='gallery galleryid-49888 gallery-columns-1 gallery-size-medium' style="content-visibility: auto;contain-intrinsic-size: auto 9724px;"><figure class='gallery-item'>
			<div class='gallery-icon landscape'>
				<img decoding="async" width="900" height="700" src="https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-2.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium" alt="The ingredients for Croatian Paprenjaci recipe are laid out on a table." srcset="https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-2.jpg 900w, https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-2-250x194.jpg 250w, https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-2-768x597.jpg 768w, https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-2-735x572.jpg 735w" sizes="(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px"  loading="lazy" fetchpriority="low"/>
			</div></figure><figure class='gallery-item'>
