			<script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"http:\/\/schema.org","@type":"Recipe","name":"Croatian Paprenjaci Recipe (Black Pepper Cookies)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Chasing the Donkey"},"datePublished":"2020-04-13","description":"Here is how to make Croatian paprenjaci. A kind of Croatian version of gingerbread cookies but with lots of black pepper as one of the main ingredients.","image":["https:\/\/chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26-480x480.jpg","https:\/\/chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26-480x360.jpg","https:\/\/chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26.jpg","https:\/\/chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26-480x270.jpg","https:\/\/chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/01\/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26-735x626.jpg"],"recipeCategory":"Croatian Recipes In English","recipeCuisine":"Croatian Desserts","recipeIngredient":["2 eggs","250 g sugar (1 1\/4 cups)","250 g honey (3\/4 cup)","250 g butter (2 sticks) ","1 tablespoon pork fat","450 g walnuts (3 3\/4 cups)","1 kg flour (7 cups)","3 tablespoons cinnamon, ground","1 tablespoon nutmeg","1 tablespoon pepper, ground","5-6 pieces of crushed or ground cloves","1 pinch of cardamom","1 lemon peel"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Whisk the butter and pork fat till it becomes foamy, add the other ingredients except for the flour, and combine well","position":1,"name":"Whisk the butter and pork fat till it...","url":"https:\/\/www.chasingthedonkey.com\/croatian-cooking-how-to-make-croatian-paprenjaci-black-pepper-cookies\/#mv_create_35_1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Then add the flour, little by little. Mix the dough that will form out of that mixture until it starts to fall off your fingers (it will take some time, but it pays off)","position":2,"name":"Then add the flour, little by little. Mix...","url":"https:\/\/www.chasingthedonkey.com\/croatian-cooking-how-to-make-croatian-paprenjaci-black-pepper-cookies\/#mv_create_35_2"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Allow the dough to rest for 2 hours in the refrigerator, wrapped in cling film","position":3,"name":"Allow the dough to rest for 2 hours...","url":"https:\/\/www.chasingthedonkey.com\/croatian-cooking-how-to-make-croatian-paprenjaci-black-pepper-cookies\/#mv_create_35_3"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the dough between two pieces of parchment paper, and roll out the dough - do not add flour to the surface. Flip the dough over several times as you roll it. Roll to the thickness of about 1\/2 cm, then using wooden molds or a glass, or another type of small cookie cutter, and cut out the cookies to your desired shape","position":4,"name":"Place the dough between two pieces of parchment...","url":"https:\/\/www.chasingthedonkey.com\/croatian-cooking-how-to-make-croatian-paprenjaci-black-pepper-cookies\/#mv_create_35_4"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"If you have the traditional wooden mold, gently press it over the dough, so it shapes the different textures and then use the knife to cut out the cookies (as the wooden mold doesn\u2019t cut them all the way trough)","position":5,"name":"If you have the traditional wooden mold, gently...","url":"https:\/\/www.chasingthedonkey.com\/croatian-cooking-how-to-make-croatian-paprenjaci-black-pepper-cookies\/#mv_create_35_5"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Place the cookies on a greased and dusted pan and bake over a moderate heat of 180\u00b0C (350\u00b0F). When they turn golden, they are done, it usually takes around 8-12 minutes","position":6,"name":"Place the cookies on a greased and dusted...","url":"https:\/\/www.chasingthedonkey.com\/croatian-cooking-how-to-make-croatian-paprenjaci-black-pepper-cookies\/#mv_create_35_6"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":4.7,"reviewCount":"26"},"url":"https:\/\/www.chasingthedonkey.com\/croatian-cooking-how-to-make-croatian-paprenjaci-black-pepper-cookies\/"}</script>	<section id="mv-creation-35" class="mv-create-card mv-create-card-35 mv-recipe-card mv-create-card-style-big-image mv-no-js mv-create-center-cards mv-create-has-uppercase mv-create-aggressive-lists mv-create-has-image " style="position: relative;">
		
		<div class="mv-create-wrapper">

			
			<header class="mv-create-header">
				<img decoding="async" src="https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26-735x626.jpg" class="mv-create-image no_pin ggnoads" data-pin-nopin="true" data-pin-description="" alt="How To Make Paprenjaci Recipe 26" srcset="https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26-735x626.jpg 735w, https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26-250x213.jpg 250w, https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26-768x655.jpg 768w, https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-pin-media="https://chasingthedonkey.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2020/01/How-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26.jpg" width="735" height="626" loading="lazy" fetchpriority="low"><div class="mv-pinterest-btn mv-pinterest-btn-right-inside" data-mv-pinterest-desc="Croatian%20Paprenjaci%20Recipe%20%28Black%20Pepper%20Cookies%29" data-mv-pinterest-img-src="https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chasingthedonkey.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2FHow-To-Make-Paprenjaci-Recipe-26.jpg" data-mv-pinterest-url="https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chasingthedonkey.com%2Fcroatian-cooking-how-to-make-croatian-paprenjaci-black-pepper-cookies%2F"></div>

<div class="mv-create-title-container">

	
	
	<h2 class="mv-create-title mv-create-title-primary"><span>Croatian Paprenjaci Recipe (Black Pepper Cookies)</span></h2>

</div>
			</header>

					<div class="mv-create-description">
			<p>Here is how to make Croatian paprenjaci. A kind of Croatian version of gingerbread cookies but with lots of black pepper as one of the main ingredients.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="mv-create-meta-flex">

		<form class="mv-create-print-form">
			<button class="mv-create-button mv-create-print-button mv-create-uppercase" data-mv-print="https://www.chasingthedonkey.com/wp-json/mv-create/v1/creations/35/print?ajax=true">
				Print			</button>
		</form>

					<div class="mv-create-reviews-flex">
				<div id="mv-create-35" class="mv-create-reviews" data-mv-create-id="35" data-mv-create-rating="4.7" data-mv-create-total-ratings="26" data-mv-rest-url="https://www.chasingthedonkey.com/wp-json/"></div>
			</div>
			</div>
<div class="mv-create-target mv-create-primary-unit"><div class="mv_slot_target" data-slot="recipe"></div></div>	<div class="mv-create-ingredients">
		<h3 class="mv-create-ingredients-title mv-create-title-secondary">Ingredients</h3>

											<ul>
									<li>
						2 eggs					</li>
									<li>
						250 g sugar (1 1/4 cups)					</li>
									<li>
						250 g honey (3/4 cup)					</li>
									<li>
						250 g butter (2 sticks) 					</li>
									<li>
						1 tablespoon pork fat					</li>
									<li>
						450 g walnuts (3 3/4 cups)					</li>
									<li>
						1 kg flour (7 cups)					</li>
									<li>
						3 tablespoons cinnamon, ground					</li>
									<li>
						1 tablespoon nutmeg					</li>
									<li>
						1 tablespoon pepper, ground					</li>
									<li>
						5-6 pieces of crushed or ground cloves					</li>
									<li>
						1 pinch of cardamom					</li>
									<li>
						1 lemon peel					</li>
							</ul>
			</div>
		<div class="mv-create-hands-free"></div>
		<div class="mv-create-instructions mv-create-instructions-slot-v2">
		<h3 class="mv-create-instructions-title mv-create-title-secondary">Instructions</h3>
		<ol><li id="mv_create_35_1">Whisk the butter and pork fat till it becomes foamy, add the other ingredients except for the flour, and combine well</li><li id="mv_create_35_2">Then add the flour, little by little. Mix the dough that will form out of that mixture until it starts to fall off your fingers (it will take some time, but it pays off)</li><li id="mv_create_35_3">Allow the dough to rest for 2 hours in the refrigerator, wrapped in cling film</li><li id="mv_create_35_4">Place the dough between two pieces of parchment paper, and roll out the dough - do not add flour to the surface. Flip the dough over several times as you roll it. Roll to the thickness of about 1/2 cm, then using wooden molds or a glass, or another type of small cookie cutter, and cut out the cookies to your desired shape</li><li id="mv_create_35_5">If you have the traditional wooden mold, gently press it over the dough, so it shapes the different textures and then use the knife to cut out the cookies (as the wooden mold doesn&rsquo;t cut them all the way trough)</li><li id="mv_create_35_6">Place the cookies on a greased and dusted pan and bake over a moderate heat of 180&deg;C (350&deg;F). When they turn golden, they are done, it usually takes around 8-12 minutes</li></ol>	</div>
	<div class="mv-create-notes mv-create-notes-slot-v2">
		<h3 class="mv-create-notes-title mv-create-title-secondary">Notes</h3>
		<div class="mv-create-notes-content">
			<p><p><strong>Store the paprenjaci in a cookie jar or another airtight container for at least 10 days before serving</strong></p></p>
		</div>
	</div>

		</div>

		<footer class="mv-create-footer">
			
